Convert Gene Symbol to Ensembl Identifier

Convert Gene Symbol to Ensembl Identifier

symbol2gene(object, ...)

# S4 method for character
symbol2gene(object, organism)

# S4 method for data.frame
symbol2gene(object, organism)

# S4 method for DataFrame
symbol2gene(object, organism)

# S4 method for dgCMatrix
symbol2gene(object, organism)

# S4 method for dgTMatrix
symbol2gene(object, organism)

# S4 method for matrix
symbol2gene(object, organism)

Arguments

object

Object.
...

Additional arguments (for the S4 generic definition).
organism

Organism name.

Value

Same class as original object.

See also

detectOrganism().

Other Gene Annotation Utilities: annotable, detectOrganism, gene2symbolFromGTF, gene2symbol, tx2geneFromGTF, tx2gene

Examples

# character
symbol2gene(c("Gnai3", "Pbsn"), organism = "mouse")
#> Mus musculus Ensembl 88 annotations
#>                Gnai3                 Pbsn 
#> "ENSMUSG00000000001" "ENSMUSG00000000003" 


# NOT RUN {
# matrix
matrix(
    data = seq(1L:4L),
    byrow = TRUE,
    nrow = 2L,
    ncol = 2L,
    dimnames = list(c("Gnai3", "Pbsn"),
                    c("sample1", "sample2"))) %>%
    symbol2gene(organism = "mouse")
# }
